    ListIterator is a special type of iterator for lists in Java that lets you traverse in both directions.

	Key points (short & simple):

	Can move forward (next()) and backward (previous()).

	Can add, remove, or update elements while iterating.

	Works only with List (ArrayList, LinkedList, etc.), not with general Set or Map.	

    differecen between 

    | Feature                   | `Iterator`                     | `ListIterator`                                          |
	| ------------------------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |
	| **Direction**             | Forward only (`next()`)        | Forward (`next()`) & backward (`previous()`)            |
	| **Supported collections** | Any Collection (`List`, `Set`) | Only `List` (`ArrayList`, `LinkedList`)                 |
	| **Modification**          | Can `remove()` element         | Can `add()`, `remove()`, `set()` (update element)       |
	| **Index info**            | No                             | Yes, can get index with `nextIndex()`/`previousIndex()` |
    

    
	
