Q:fail-fast vs fail-safe ? 
	Fail Fast and Fail Safe are ways of handling errors or failures in a program.

	Fail Fast:

	Stops immediately when an error is found.

	Example: A list iterator throws an exception if the list is modified while iterating.


	Fail Safe:

	Continues working even when there is an error.

	Example: A concurrent collection (like CopyOnWriteArrayList) allows safe iteration even if modified.


	In short:

	Fail Fast: Detects issues early and stops.

	Fail Safe: Handles issues without stopping.												
	
